  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Investigators say the late publishing magnate Robert Maxwell siphoned money from his companies in an attempt
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   to deal with crushing debts.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   A government prosecution agency investigating his Mirror Group pension fund assets says
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   that $630 million was taken from the fund without authority.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   His son Kevin says the debts are so enormous nothing is left for the pensioners.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   Reportedly, Maxwell never created the pension fund promised to New York Daily News managers.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   Creditors face losses of $905 million.
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   Kevin admitted his father was a crook,
  </a>
